Quote: Abbreviated local rhyming slang is also used. `I'd love an aristotle of alison' means `I'd love a bottle of bourbon' - bourbon rhyming with Alison Durbin. [a NZ singer of ?1960s] Meths is blue or white lady, and steam is a mixture of meths and sherry.
